xbrlcore.dimensions
Class Hypercube

java.lang.Object
  xbrlcore.dimensions.Hypercube
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Hypercube
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

This class represents an Hypercube as it is described by the Dimensions 1.0 Specification which can be obtained from http://www.xbrl.org/SpecRecommendations/.

A Hypercube consists of one or multiple dimensions which are represented by xbrlcore.dimensions.Dimension objects. It describes which dimensions and which domain a primary item can be reported for.

A Hypercube always consists of an XBRL concept representing it and a set of Dimensions.

Author:
Daniel Hamm

Method Detail

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
This method tests for "equality" between two Hypercube objects. They are equal if:
- the concepts representing both Hypercubes are equal
- the set of Dimensions of both Hypercubes are equal
- both Hypercubes are defined in the same extended link role

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object
Returns:
True if both Hypercube objects are equal, false otherwise.

addHypercube

public void addHypercube(Hypercube newCube)
                  throws java.lang.CloneNotSupportedException
Adds all the dimensions / domain member of a second hypercube to this hypercube. This is done in the following way: If the second hypercube has a dimension which is not contained in this cube, the dimension and all its domain members are added to this cube. If the second hypercube has a dimension which is already contained in this cube, all domain members of this dimension of the second cube which are not part of the same dimension of this cube are added to this cube.

Parameters:
newCube - The second cube whose dimension/domain members are added to this cube.
Throws:
java.lang.CloneNotSupportedException

hasDimensionCombination

public boolean hasDimensionCombination(MultipleDimensionType mdt)
Checks whether this hypercube contains specific dimension/domain member combinations.

Parameters:
mdt - Object describing the specific dimension/domain member combinations for which this hypercube is checkted.
Returns:
True if and only if this hypercube contains all the dimension/domain member combinations described in the given MultipleDimensionType object. The hypercube also must not contain additinal dimension/domain member combinations than those which are contained in the given MultipleDimensinType object. Otherwise false is returned.
